news.news: Haliburton finished Monday's 113-99 victory over the Nets with 23 points (5-12 FG, 4-7 3Pt, 9-9 FT), two rebounds, eight assists, one block and one steal across 32 minutes.
news.analysis: Haliburton departed Monday's contest with an ankle injury in the second quarter, but he didn't have problems managing his workload the rest of the way and finished with a solid stat line. He ended just two dimes away from a double-double, but on the other hand, it was his 15th straight game with at least seven assists. Over that stretch, Haliburton has experienced a sizable uptick in his numbers, averaging 19.6 points and 9.3 assists per contest.
